        <bubbleHelp>If checked the system will search for cargo that is 
currently overstowed by cargo for another voyage.  
This will just show cargo that is overstowed by items for 
a different voyage, or for the same voyage but with a different
 discharge port (in the same way the new Is Overstowed column will work).</bubbleHelp>
        <enabled/>
        <height>17</height>
        <left>21</left>
        <top>122</top>
        <visible/>
        <width>200</width>
    </CMUI_CheckBox>
    <CMUI_CheckBox name="chkGroundPos" id="5da54c12-b292-4353-8c74-e83dcbe654a7">
        <caption>Ground Position/ No Overstow</caption>
        <transparent/>
        <fontSize>8.25</fontSize>
        <foreColor>-2147483640</foreColor>
        <parent name="5129::CMUI_QueryEnquiry::shtQuery5"/>
        <parentBottomOffset>172</parentBottomOffset>
        <parentRightOffset>25</parentRightOffset>
        <show3D>3</show3D>
        <tabIndex>606</tabIndex>
        <tabStop/>
        <backColor>-2147483633</backColor>
        <bubbleHelp>If checked the system will search for cargo that
 is in a ground position with no overstows.  This is 
to highlight cargo that can potentially 
be moved to consolidate it.</bubbleHelp>
        <enabled/>
        <height>17</height>
        <left>21</left>
        <top>95</top>
        <visible/>
        <width>200</width>
    </CMUI_CheckBox>
    <CMUI_CheckBox name="chkTopPos" id="0e17d935-6d1c-413c-9f53-4e7d495a0324">
        <caption>Top Position Cargo</caption>
        <transparent/>
